[SN]TITLE[SN]
Teen 'seriously assaulted' in Glasgow city centre

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 17-year-old has suffered serious injuries in an early-morning incident in the centre of Glasgow.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The teenager was taken to Glasgow Royal Infirmary but was released after treatment.
Gordon Street, at the main entrance to Glasgow Central Station, was closed after the incident at about 03:45.
Police said a 32-year-old man would be the subject of a report to the procurator fiscal in relation to an alleged assault.
The road re-opened to vehicles at about 08:40.
